00:02:15.620 --> 00:02:16.620
I had time.

00:02:16.620 --> 00:02:19.150
I had time on a scale that no one can imagine
today.

00:02:19.150 --> 00:02:21.900
You know, no e-mail, no distractions.

00:02:21.900 --> 00:02:29.610
I read the entire 6,000 pages of Cooks Journals
one winter and then I came down.

00:02:29.610 --> 00:02:30.880
And so Iím gonna thank a few people.

00:02:30.880 --> 00:02:35.310
The book that Iím here for was published
yesterday, so itís still, still a new thing.

00:02:35.310 --> 00:02:39.340
First of all, my sister Esther, who some of
you probably know.

00:02:39.340 --> 00:02:45.230
Sheís played a role in a lot of the start
ups here and in Silicon Valley she actually,

00:02:45.230 --> 00:02:49.820
I think, had some of the original investment
in Google at the very beginning.

00:02:49.820 --> 00:02:53.200
There she is with her friend Bill in 1984.

00:02:53.200 --> 00:02:58.850
And Esther was very kind to sort of extract
her brother from the Canadian wilderness and

00:02:58.850 --> 00:03:03.720
