00:11:28.740 --> 00:11:33.720
Now I work in a bar, old bar in Bellingham
Washington so I could lay out, you know, one

00:11:33.720 --> 00:11:36.430
by one, the chapters.

00:11:36.430 --> 00:11:41.760
So Turing comes into the picture because,
you know, the conception of all this goes

00:11:41.760 --> 00:11:42.760
back to Turing.

00:11:42.760 --> 00:11:46.510
Turing came to Princeton in 1936, he stayed
for two years.

00:11:46.510 --> 00:11:50.650
He worked fairly closely with Johnny Von Neumann
who always credited Turing.

00:11:50.650 --> 00:11:56.840
Von Neumann always said, ìThe original idea
was Turingís, all I did was implement it.î

00:11:56.840 --> 00:12:03.390
And why we now have an incredible divisive
battle going on between people who think the

00:12:03.390 --> 00:12:07.990
Americanís get too much credit, people who
think that British get too much credit and

00:12:07.990 --> 00:12:11.740
at the time both sides were absolutely collaborating
with each other.

00:12:11.740 --> 00:12:16.520
There was not rivalry until, sort of, the
historians who came in later.

00:12:16.520 --> 00:12:21.130
In 1950 Alan Turing whoís very interested
in the, the whole idea of what we now call,

00:12:21.130 --> 00:12:26.990
